  "prompt": "Do all MSI laptop's steel series keyboards light up?",
  "response": "No, not all MSI laptops with SteelSeries keyboards have backlighting. While MSI often partners with SteelSeries for their keyboards, and many of these keyboards *do* feature RGB or single-color backlighting, it's not a universal feature across their entire laptop lineup.\n\nHere's a breakdown:\n\n*   **High-End Models:** Generally, the higher-end MSI laptops (like those in the GE, GT, and Raider series) almost always have per-key RGB backlighting on their SteelSeries keyboards.\n*   **Mid-Range Models:** Some mid-range models (like certain versions of the Stealth, Creator, or Katana series) may have either per-key RGB, single-color backlighting (usually red or white), or no backlighting at all, depending on the specific configuration and model year.\n*   **Entry-Level Models:** Lower-end or older models are less likely to have any backlighting on their SteelSeries keyboards. They might use a simpler keyboard design instead.\n\n**How to Determine if a Specific Model has Backlighting:**\n\n1.  **Check the Product Specifications:** The most reliable way is to consult the official product page or specifications sheet on the MSI website for the specific model you're interested in. Look for terms like \"SteelSeries keyboard with per-key RGB backlight,\" \"single-color backlight,\" or simply \"backlit keyboard.\" If the spec doesn't list backlighting, it most likely does not have it.\n2.  **Read Reviews:** Professional reviews of the laptop often mention the keyboard and whether it has backlighting.\n3.  **Examine Images/Videos:** Look at high-resolution images or videos of the laptop. If the keys are clearly illuminated, it has backlighting.\n4.  **Ask the Seller:** If you're buying from a retailer, ask them directly. Be sure to specify the exact model number.\n5.  **MSI Center:** MSI's preinstalled software for some laptops allows you to customize your lighting options. If you have it installed and see lighting settings, it should mean your keyboard is backlit.\n\n**In summary, while SteelSeries keyboards on MSI laptops are often associated with backlighting, it's not a guarantee. Always verify the specific model's features before making a purchase.**\n",
